# Project 8 - Enterprise Mini Project

## Overview
Designed and implemented a multi-site enterprise network using VLAN segmentation, router-on-a-stick, DHCP, and OSPF routing.

## Topology
- Site A: VLAN 10 (Users), VLAN 20 (Admin)
- Site B: VLAN 30 (Users), VLAN 40 (Servers)
- WAN: 10.0.0.0/30 using OSPF Area 0

## Technologies
- VLANs
- Trunking
- Router-on-a-Stick
- DHCP
- OSPF
- Ping and CLI verification

## Verification
- VLAN communication tested
- Inter-VLAN routing verified
- Cross-site connectivity confirmed
- DHCP assignment validated
- OSPF neighbor relationship established
- Routing tables checked

## Result
All devices successfully communicated across VLANs and sites. Dynamic routing via OSPF ensured scalability.

## Skills Demonstrated
- Network design
- Troubleshooting
- CLI verification
- Documentation
